features: HONEYCOMB NONSTICK PAN - Combined honeycomb raised technology with non-stick coating, these honeycomb pans perform well in nonstick cooking and cleanup. No foods stick on and can be cleaned quickly and easily after cooking.

SUPERIOR HEAT CONDUCTION PERFORMANCE - Our stainless steel pans conduct heat quickly and evenly with precise temperature control because of triply stainless steel system with aluminum core. This is where you really start to get great cooking results.

SCRATCH RESISTANT - The stainless steel frying pans have excellent scratch resistance thank to the raised honeycomb stainless steel protective barrier. You actually can use metal utensils with rounded edges in these nonstick frying pans.

OMNIPOTENT FRYING PAN - These frying pans with lids can be used with gas, electric, induction cooktops, and even oven or broiler. Sear, fry, sauté, or bake with these frying pans, everything is such easy and enjoy the fun of cooking in your heart!

THE PERFECT COMBINATION - The stainless steel frying pan set with lid includes 9.5-inch and 11-inch skillets, which can meet your needs for cooking any dishes. Both pans with lids can be used in dishwasher.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Honeycomb Frying Pan With Lid For The Everyday Cooking A welcome addition to any kitchen This nonstick pan is constructed from premium quality aluminum alloy for quick and even heating, and meets the different needs of everyday cooking. Triple-layer nonstick interior with stylish honeycomb provides extra durability and wear-resistance.Ergonomically designed long handle is comfortable grip & easy to lift and pour.Works well on all types of stovetops including induction.Dishwasher safe, although hand wash is recommended.Oven safe up to 500°F.

INCREASED STEEL MESH AREA With fully covered honeycomb interior, the steel pan has outstanding nonstick performance than other nonstick pans. VERTICAL GLASS LID Durable glass lids give you a front-row seat to your meal and also easily stand on your countertop. STAINLESS STEEL BOTTOM Steel bottom makes the pan induction compatible, and it also helps with heat retention and even heating.

Michelangelo Kitchenware Shaped it with experience, sharpened it with precision, crafted with innovative technology, and checked it with a meticulous German eye, Michelangelo Kitchenware is dedicated to design and manufacture the most beautiful, innovative, and performing kitchenware to every cooking enthusiasts. Originated in Haan Germany since 1931, Michelangelo is proudly celebrating its 90 years anniversary and carry on its mission to bring German-Standard kitchen products to every family in the world.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Replaced my hexclad
reviews.reviewText: I have the 12 inch Hexclad and that was decent, love that that was easy to clean. My wife still complains that Heclad was still too sticky. So after buying the Michelangelo wok, I purchase this pan. It's absolutely better than Hexclad. Pan heats up hot, and made perfect eggs with some bacon fat with medium low heat. Easy to clean, not sticking to pan as much as the Hexclad. Hopefully this pan will last forever.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These work like Hexclad at a fraction of the price. Heats up faster on my induction cooktop than my Costco non-stick pans. These do stick a bit with eggs and such if you don't use oil or butter, but cleans up easily anyway. I like the way it heats up the food efficiently. I like it comes with the glass lid that has a stand-up handle. Well made stainless rim, better than Hexclad.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars About as good as Hexclad at cheaper price and will last a lifetime
reviews.reviewText: I have a full set of Hexclad pots and pans which I absolutely love. I needed one additional 8-inch pan, and rather than buy another Hexclad pan which costs $160 with a lid, I thought I'd give this MICHELANGELO pan a try since it would only be secondary pan in my collection. Like the Hexclad, the MICHELANGELO pan has a surface comprised of thousands of stainless steel nubs which are surrounded with recessed non-stick material. The result is a pan that is nearly indestructible and will last a lifetime. You can use metal utensils, steel wool, Bar Keepers Friend cleaner, etc. without harming or delaminating the recessed non-stick material which would otherwise be a concern with typical non-stick pans.Two important considerations for using these pans:1. Season the pans before first time use by placing a teaspoon or two of avocado oil in the pans for 2-3 minutes on medium heat, then let the pan cool and wipe off the excess oil.2. To maximize the non-stick qualities of this pan, use much lower heat settings than you'd use in other pans. Because of the stainless steel, these pans can get much hotter than other pans. If you don't lower the heat, food may stick. Not a problem though with lower heat settings! For example, if you cook eggs at a heat setting of 4 with other pans, use a heat seating of 2.5 with these pans.If you are looking for a good pan that you will never need to replace and at a reasonable price, try these!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Nice little frypan. Perfect weight and size. Durable handle that doesn’t get too hot to hold when cooking. Included glass lid also has an angled handle that allows it to stay cool and easy to grip. All cookware should come with this type of lid handle! I also got this particular pan because it’s also induction capable even though it’s mostly used on a gas stove. I also like that you can use metal utensils as there’s no Teflon or other type of nonstick surface that would be ruined using metal utensils. BUT, it’s NOT nonstick as advertised. I’m ok with that though, just use oil etc. and put things in it after it’s hot. It’s a sturdy, perfectly weighted pan that has a nice appearance, especially the interior surface - nice design. I got the 8”, looking to purchase the full size frypan as well now too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars It is not "Nonstick" cookware.
reviews.reviewText: The pan was seasoned with olive oil and I cooked my one egg with mushrooms for breakfast. I could not slide the egg out. It would not slide out even when I slammed the pan on its side onto the paper plate. I had to pry it out with my fork and it left pieces on the pan. It did wash up easily.The pan etching is beautiful if you want to decorate your kitchen.i used it on my induction cook top at 75%.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Pan seems to be of high quality. As others have mentioned, not quite as non-stick as some others, but not bad, and easy to clean. My 9.5 inch size is perfect for me, and it is nice to have a wide variety of other sizes to choose from. The handle for the lid is not to my liking, mainly because it is harder to store; but this is a matter of taste, and some might like that it is easier to hold. Looks like it will last, but of course only time will tell.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Doesn't handle egg whites well.....
reviews.reviewText: I tried and tried and tried to like this. I used avocado oil, grapeseed oil and butter. Egg whites will always burn. I tried it on an induction oven and an electric oven without success. I've had Teflon skillets that act a lot better with minimal to no oil and no sticking. Other foods might fare well... Like meat or vegetables. But egg whites are out. It is sturdy and distributes heat well.The design is pretty. But I have better cast iron skillets that will do a better job. They hyped the non-stick up a little too much. If you let your burned food in the skillet sit in water... It does seem to clean up nicely without sticking. I don't cook on high heat... I cook on medium to medium low... With the same result. I'm glad I only brought the 8 in. I would have been pissed at the 9 or 12 in

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought these because we were getting an induction stove and our aluminum pans wouldn't work. After almost a year I can say they are great! 1. They are so easy to clean. Usually just a quick swish with a dishrag is all they need. They haven't seen the dishwasher yet. 2. The lids are also great. One for each pan. The handle is designed so you can place them vertically. 3. After almost a year they look just as new as they did when they came. Excellent product! Buy them with confidence.
Además de la fina artesanía, es un gusto usarlo. Excelentes propiedades antiadherentes t muy fácil de ser lavado. Una compra muy recomendable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on October 20, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Since my wife had a stroke, I have taken over cooking duties. I was frustrated by not having a large frying pan with a lid. I also wanted a pan that could be used on the stove top and in the oven. This one fits the bill, at a price. It is very solidly constructed (i.e. heavy) with a nicely fitting glass lid that has a large handle. The non-stick surface is (apparently) environmentally friendly and has a honeycomb pattern of the base material. The sales blurb says that you can safely use a metal spatula if it has rounded edges. Which raises one negative point--there were no care instructions included, no dos and don'ts. This seems odd for such a pricey item. I would like to know how to take care of it in the long term.
Vengono vendute come antiaderenti ma non lo sono. Scorretti.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on November 30, 2022
reviews.reviewText: This new honeycomb technology is great. Its relatively non-stick, however things do still tend to stick if you don't use any oil.The heat distribution is great, food cooks evenly and its nice to know that using metal kitchen utensils are safe to use!I've had the small frying pan for months and it still looks brand new, would recommend :)
